course_metadata.title: ECONOMICS AND HOUSING POLICIES FOR DECARBONISATION AND ENERGY MANAGEMENT

content_chunks.content: The key aspects of reaching the aim are centred around the energy efficiency of buildings, different variations of green and sustainable construction, building energy management and energy communities, financial incentives and stimulus for the improvement of the energy performance of buildings, the integration and use of different renewable energy sources in buildings, as well as the application of the circularity principle to the use and maintenance of buildings. The course allows students to explore different aspects of the decarbonization of energy and the building sector, as well as national economies, by providing structured, well-rounded and professionally sound information about the role of the built environment, cities and single buildings in the European decarbonization process. The course is based on a blend of socio-economic, engineering and economic aspects of decarbonization of the built environment, which demonstrates an interdisciplinary outlook on processes creating, directing and influencing technologically sufficient and socio-economically justifies decarbonization pathways of existing European building stock.

Technology for building decarbonization and energy management policy implementation - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in housing policy economics and building decarbonization strategies using advanced energy efficiency management and sustainable construction techniques. Students will master green building incentives design, energy cooperatives development, and community energy initiatives implementation for optimal renewable energy integration and solar energy systems deployment. The curriculum focuses on practical heat pump technology applications, energy demand management strategies, and life cycle assessment (LCA) methodologies for circular economy principles integration. Participants will gain hands-on experience with passive energy buildings design, zero energy buildings development, and plus energy buildings construction using green hydrogen infrastructure and building energy monitoring systems. The program emphasizes renovation strategies optimization, healthy housing principles implementation, and energy policy frameworks development for comprehensive green gas technologies, micro-cogeneration systems, and green roofs and facades integration in sustainable building environments.
